
     tvDMX  (c) 1992,93		Randolph Beck
     =====


About tvDMX Commands
====================

    Most tvDMX commands are defined in unit DMXGIZMA with a constant that
    is defined relative to constant cmDMX.  Constant cmDMX is based on the
    constant defined as FirstCmdNum = 4400, which is defined in unit RSET.
    tvDMX reserves commands 4400 through 4999 for its own use, but you can
    change this to prevent conflicts by modifying FirstCmdNum or cmDMX.

	    cmBeep			cmChime
	    cmToggleSound		cmToggleVideo
	    cmUserScreen		FirstCmdNum

	    cmDMX			cmDMX_Ack
	    cmDMX_Bottom		cmDMX_DoubleClick
	    cmDMX_Down			cmDMX_Draw
	    cmDMX_DrawData		cmDMX_End
	    cmDMX_Enter			cmDMX_FieldAltered
	    cmDMX_FixSize		cmDMX_goto
	    cmDMX_Home			cmDMX_Left
	    cmDMX_Lock			cmDMX_LockData
	    cmDMX_NextRow		cmDMX_PgDn
	    cmDMX_PgUp			cmDMX_RecIndClicked
	    cmDMX_Reset			cmDMX_Right
	    cmDMX_RollCall		cmDMX_ScreenBottom
	    cmDMX_ScreenTop		cmDMX_ScrollBarChanged
	    cmDMX_SetupRecord		cmDMX_Top
	    cmDMX_Unlock		cmDMX_UnlockData
	    cmDMX_Up			cmDMX_WrongKey
	    cmDMX_XXXX			cmDMX_ZeroizeField
	    cmDMX_ZeroizeRecord

	    cmPRN_EndPage		cmPRN_FormFeed
	    cmPRN_LineFeed		cmPRN_NewPage
	    cmPRN_Reset			cmPRN_SetOptions



CONSTANTS
---------

    cmBeep		= cmDMX + 54;

	TAppA.HandleEvent() beeps if BeepOn is TRUE.  See cmToggleSound.


    cmChime		= cmDMX + 55;

	Broadcast every 30 minutes by object TTimeView.


    cmDMX		= FirstCmdNum;

	Command constant reserved for future use.  All tvDMX commands
	constants are based on this number.  (See also FirstCmdNum below.)


    cmDMX_XXXX		= 

	Record and/or Field movement commands:
	    cmDMX_Enter			cmDMX_Left
	    cmDMX_Right			cmDMX_Home
	    cmDMX_End			cmDMX_goto
	    cmDMX_NextRow		cmDMX_Up
	    cmDMX_Down			cmDMX_PgUp
	    cmDMX_PgDn			cmDMX_ScreenTop
	    cmDMX_ScreenBottom		cmDMX_Top
	    cmDMX_Bottom

	These commands are issued internally when the user changes fields
	or records.  They are processed only after validation by Valid().
	You can override the Valid() method to test for data validity when
	one of these commands is given.  Example:

	  function  TMyDmx.Valid (Command : word) : boolean;
	  var  V : boolean;
	  begin
	    V := inherited Valid (Command);
	    If V and
	      (Command >= cmDMX_Left) and (Command <= cmDMX_Bottom) and
	      (CurrentField <> nil) and
	      (CurrentField^.fieldnum = 3) and
	      (PRealNum(FieldData)^ > 15000.0)
	     then
	      begin
	      Vidis := TRUE;
	      MessageBox ('Number too big.', nil, mfError or mfOKButton);
	      Vidis := FALSE;
	      V := FALSE;
	      end;
	    Valid := V;
	  end;

	This example prevents the user from entering over 15000 in field 3.
	It assumes that field 3 is a TYPE TRealNum field (see RSET.PAS).
	Note how the Vidis flag must be used to prevent resetting the view
	when the message box is activated.


    cmDMX_Ack		= cmDMX +  2;

	Command event sent to a view to acknowledge a roll call broadcast.
	This command will only be received by views that send cmDMX_RollCall
	broadcasts/commands.  The cmDMX_RollCall / cmDMX_Ack combination can
	be used to determine if any tvDMX views share the same data.


    cmDMX_Bottom	= cmDMX + 29;

	See cmDMX_XXXX control commands.


    cmDMX_DoubleClick	= cmDMX + 30;

	This command is issued when a field gets a valid double-click.


    cmDMX_Down		= cmDMX + 23;

	See cmDMX_XXXX control commands.


    cmDMX_Draw		= cmDMX +  4;

	Should be used by TDmxScroller derivatives only.  This broadcast
	forces all tvDMX views that access this data to redraw the view.
	This command is broadcast by TDmxEditor views when they become
	unfocused --to ensure that changes are reflected in other windows.
	InfoPtr should be set to @Self.


    cmDMX_DrawData	= cmDMX +  5;

	Broadcast call to be used by non-tvDMX views to force the tvDMX views
	that use the data at InfoPtr^ to redraw.  For example, a dialog box
	in SAMPLES.PAS calls this function before exit:

	    Message (DeskTop, evBroadcast, cmDMX_DrawData, @BusyData);

	This makes sure that changes made by the dialog box are reflected
	in all tvDMX views which access the BusyData array.


    cmDMX_End		= cmDMX + 19;
    cmDMX_Enter		= cmDMX + 15;

	See cmDMX_XXXX control commands.


    cmDMX_FieldAltered	= cmDMX +  3;

	Broadcast event sent by EvaluateField() to the view's owner after a
	field has been altered.  This is especially useful in dialog boxes.


    cmDMX_FixSize	= cmDMX + 10;

	Broadcast call to ensure that tvDMX windows have not become wider than
	they were originally designed.  This event should be broadcast after
	cascade or tile operations are conducted.  Application object TAppA
	sends this broadcast when handling the cmCascade and cmTile commands.


    cmDMX_goto		= cmDMX + 20;
    cmDMX_Home		= cmDMX + 18;
    cmDMX_Left		= cmDMX + 16;

	See cmDMX_XXXX control commands.


    cmDMX_Lock		= cmDMX +  6;
    cmDMX_Unlock	= cmDMX +  8;

	Should be used by TDmxScroller derivatives only.  This broadcast
	forces all tvDMX views that access this data to set/reset the Locked
	field, which will prevent the user from altering data in that view.
	InfoPtr should be set to @Self.


    cmDMX_LockData	= cmDMX +  7;
    cmDMX_UnlockData	= cmDMX +  9;

	Broadcast call to be used by non-tvDMX views to force the tvDMX views
	that use the data at InfoPtr^ to set/reset the Locked field.


    cmDMX_NextRow	= cmDMX + 21;
    cmDMX_PgDn		= cmDMX + 25;
    cmDMX_PgUp		= cmDMX + 24;

	See cmDMX_XXXX control commands.


    cmDMX_RecIndClicked	= cmDMX + 46;

	Broadcast by TDmxRecInd when record indicator was clicked.  This
        command is tied to the "Go to Record" option in SAMPLES.EXE.


    cmDMX_Reset		= cmDMX + 49;

	Resets the size of the collection in unit tvDMXCOL.


    cmDMX_Right		= cmDMX + 17;

	See cmDMX_XXXX control commands.


    cmDMX_RollCall	= cmDMX +  1;

	Broadcast call that may be issued by any view to determine if any
	tvDMX views are on the desktop.  A tvDMX view will respond to it by
	sending a cmDMX_Ack message to the sender.
	This can also be issued as a command-event to determine if the
	selected view is a tvDMX view.


    cmDMX_ScreenBottom	= cmDMX + 27;
    cmDMX_ScreenTop	= cmDMX + 26;

	See cmDMX_XXXX control commands.


    cmDMX_ScrollBarChanged = cmDMX + 33;

	Broadcast via the tvDMX view's owner to update the TDmxLabels views
	when the scroll bars have changed.


    cmDMX_SetupRecord	= cmDMX + 11;

	Broadcast through the view's owner when the position pointer moves
	to another record.


    cmDMX_Top		= cmDMX + 28;

	See cmDMX_XXXX control commands.


    cmDMX_Unlock	= cmDMX +  8;

	See cmDMX_Lock.


    cmDMX_UnlockData	= cmDMX +  9;

	See cmDMX_LockData.


    cmDMX_Up		= cmDMX + 22;

	See cmDMX_XXXX control commands.


    cmDMX_WrongKey	= cmDMX + 12;

	Command sent to the application when a key was pressed that cannot
	be accepted (eg: text in a numeric field).  This command is handled
	by the event-handler in the TAppA object (in unit tvGIZMA).


    cmDMX_ZeroizeField	= cmDMX + 13;

	Command to delete the current field.  If Valid(cmDMX_ZeroizeField)
	is TRUE, the tvDMX view's event handler calls ZeroizeField() to
	process this command.


    cmDMX_ZeroizeRecord	= cmDMX + 14;

	Command to delete the current record.  If Valid(cmDMX_ZeroizeRecord)
	is TRUE, the tvDMX view's event handler calls ZeroizeRecord() to
	process this command.


    cmPRN_EndPage	= cmDMX + 41;

	tvDMXREP: broadcast before page end.


    cmPRN_FormFeed	= cmDMX + 44;

	tvDMXREP: send form feed to printer.


    cmPRN_LineFeed	= cmDMX + 43;

	tvDMXREP: send line feed to printer.


    cmPRN_NewPage	= cmDMX + 40;

	tvDMXREP: broadcast before new page.


    cmPRN_Reset		= cmDMX + 45;

	tvDMXREP: reset printer.


    cmPRN_SetOptions	= cmDMX + 42;

	tvDMXREP: command to open options window.


    cmToggleSound	= cmDMX + 52;

	Command handled by the TAppA object's event handler to toggle its
	BeepOn flag, and change the menubar's ON/OFF indicator.  MenuBar
	initialization with function TAppA.NewSoundItem() is recommended,
	but not required.  (See program SAMPLES.)


    cmToggleVideo	= cmDMX + 53;

	Command handled by the TAppA object's event handler to toggle the
	hi-res screen on and off, and change the menubar's 25/50 indicator.
	Use of the TAppA.NewVideoItem() function is recommended, but not
	required.  (See program SAMPLES.)


    cmUserScreen	= cmDMX + 51;

	Command handled by the TAppA object's event-handler to display the
	screen that was visible prior to the application's initialization.


    FirstCmdNum	=  4400;

	Starting number for reserved commands.  tvDMX commands are all
	based on the cmDMX constant, which is based on this value.
	tvDMX reserves commands 4400 through 4999 for its own use, but
	you can change this by modifying this constant.
	(Unit RSET)


